        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="89" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/9–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Australia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jarman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canberra</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-15T15:00:00+10:00">September 15, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 15—6:09 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. Today’s press dominated by stories Acheson–Bevin talks on Far East and
                    London rumor British withdrawing Ambassador to China and considering recognition
                    Communist regime there, also speculation that US will follow suit.</p>
                <p>In view Deptel 82, June 14, which we communicated to External Affairs, please
                    telegraph whether any changes are contemplated US policy non-recognition
                    Communists in China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jarman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
